<div class="view-header">
<div class="sectionheader">
<h3>Recent Posts</h3>
</div>
</div>
<div class="view-content">
<div class="views-row"><div class="views-field views-field-field-blog-category"><div class="field-content field-name-field-blog-category"><a href="/blog-categories/lit-lists" hreflang="en">Lit Lists</a>
</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-thumbnail"><div class="field-content imageleft"> <a href="/blog/lit-lists/perspectives-walking-lit-list-james-fawcett-madeline-meyers" hreflang="en"><img loading="lazy" src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/styles/blog_thumbnail/public/Fawcett-Anchor.jpg?itok=mvTwdl0e" width="100" height="75" alt="The covers to the books discussed below" typeof="foaf:Image" class="img-fluid image-style-blog-thumbnail" />
</a>
</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-richtitle"><h4 class="field-content"><a href="https://www.worldliteraturetoday.org/blog/lit-lists/perspectives-walking-lit-list-james-fawcett-madeline-meyers">Perspectives on Walking: A Lit List
</a>
</h4></div><div><div class="blog-summary">In the summer of 2022 I (James Fawcett) walked from Denver to Durango on the Colorado Trail. I started the walk alone and eighteen years old, having…
